label scene3a:
    scene bed_day with fade

    nrt "After you finished lunch, you’ve been dozing off and on for what might have been hours. Or maybe not. "
    
    nrt "Sometimes when that happens you feel like you’ve been asleep for days, then you check your phone and barely half an hour has passed."

    nrt "You’re not actually sure where your phone is. Presumably with your clothes, wherever Lillian took them to. "
    nrt "This place definitely looks nice enough to have a washing machine, probably even a tumble dryer, although the idea of Lillian doing your laundry for you after already looking after you so much is deeply shameful."

    nrt "Your missing phone, combined with the dimmed light from the blinds, has made time as a whole feel a little blurry. "
    nrt "Thinking about it, you’re not sure if you woke up at half-seven like you were supposed to, or if half the day had already passed by the time Lillian came in."

    nrt "The post-lunch drowsiness isn’t helping, and by this point it could be any time from midday to six, the only thing you’re reasonably sure of is the fact there’s still some daylight peeking through the blinds."

    nrt "All of this vague detachment from reality is making it hard to tether to the important things in life."

    nrt "Like the fact that {b}Lillian kissed your knuckles and called you a good girl.{/b}"

    nrt "You’re {b}pretty{/b} sure you didn’t dream that. Well OK, you’ve definitely dreamed {b}something{/b} like that in the past, more than once. But this time it actually happened, for real, to you."

    nrt "Lesbians have died for less."

    nth ne "(I just wanna know… {i}why.{/i})"

    nth ne "(Like, if Lillian’s trying to seduce me, then yeah, job done. Honestly she’d already succeeded years ago by just existing.)"

    nth ne_bl "(All the flirting at the bar and nursing me back to health and hitting me with the {i}good girl,{/i} it’s just…)"

    nrt "Are you {b}complaining?{/b}"

    nth ne_sd_bl "(No! It just feels like, I dunno, complete overkill.)"

    nth ne "(I just can’t figure out why she’s doing all this.)"

    nrt "Because it’s hot and it’s clearly working?"

    nth sa "(Well yeah, obviously. My point was more, why is she doing all this {i}to me?{/i})"

    nrt "Oh. Yes, that is a good point, actually. She {b}definitely{/b} has better options than you. Even with the sapphic dating pool being as restrictive as it is, London’s pretty famously a good city to be queer in."

    nth dj_sm "(Sure doesn’t feel like it.)"

    nrt "To you, maybe."

    nth an "(Hey I got dates at uni!)"

    nth an "(And makeouts at the SU bar! And hookups!)"

    nth ne_s "(Even a couple girlfriends.)"

    nrt "For a combined total of seven weeks."

    nth sa "(Well yeah, that’s kinda the problem I’m getting at, isn’t it.)"

    nth sa "(Finding other cute gay girls in London isn’t really the hard part, it’s finding one I have any kind of connection with at all.)"

    nrt "That’s true, you are {b}remarkably{/b} boring."

    nth an "(So were they!)"

    nth ag "(Basically all of them were just trying out being with girls for the first time.)"

    nrt "And assuming {b}you’d{/b} be capable of showing them the ropes? How unfortunate for them."

    nth an "(Oh come on, I’m pretty sure that one Portuguese girl {i}literally{/i} called me her {i}experiment.{/i})"

    nth sa "(I dunno. It just didn’t feel like any of them {i}got{/i} it.)"

    nrt "You mean, they didn’t wallow in self-pity? Didn’t consider their queerness to be primarily defined through their own isolation?"

    nth an "(I mean, kinda, yeah? Newsflash, it {i}is{/i} pretty isolating being gay and spending most of secondary school listening to all your classmates go on about which BTS boys they wanna snog.)"
    nrt "You mean you {b}don’t{/b} think they’d have loved hearing about what you wanted that evil cat girl from She-Ra to do to you?"

    nth ne_s_sd_bl "(Oh me being down bad for Catra is {b}not{/b} past tense.)"

    nth su_bl "(…Anyway.)"

    nrt "Easier to indulge in fiction than put yourself out there, as always."

    nth an "(I was {i}just{/i} explaining that all the girls I met {i}putting myself out there{/i} were basic ass white girls.)"

    nrt "A category which functionally includes you, remember."

    nth sa "(I never forget.)"

    nrt "So then why {b}not{/b} try to at least meet people you had a bit more in common with? Ciara was always pestering you to go to LGBT-Soc with her, potentially meet some lesbians who were a bit more invested than an experimental fling."

    nrt "Hell, if you were that worried about dating white girls with an Asian fetish, your uni wasn’t exactly short on Chinese girls for you to try chatting up."

    nth su "(That’s crazy. Actual Chinese girls, from Actual China?) "
    nth su "(I barely even share {b}either{/b} language with them. Most of them lost interest as soon as they found out I don’t even have a WeChat, kinda hard to pivot that first impression into smooching.)"

    nrt "And if you’d tried?"

    nth ne "(Look, it was hard enough asking them to share lecture notes, never mind find out if they were fellow fans of Chappell Roan.)"

    nrt "Did you think they’d be homophobic? Just because they came from China?"

    nat sa_sp "No! Maybe? What kind of question is that!?"

    nrt "And you think {b}this{/b} is what gives you some special connection to Lillian?"

    nat sa_sp "I never said that!"

    nrt "It was the point you were getting to. It’s not like you have anything else to offer."

    nrt "You’re a dead-end loser barely keeping herself afloat, with no prospects to speak of. "
    nrt "You crashed out of academia, then rather than try to even attempt to land on your feet, or even pivot to a career that followed from your actual undergrad degree... "
    nrt "You found the first job that would vaguely cover your rent and proceeded to waste nearly four years of your life there."

    nrt "And the one lifeline you’re holding to is that you and Lillian are both Chinese-Brits? You? You’re basically just a white girl who got called a few extra slurs in secondary school."

    nat ag_sd_sp "Shut the fuck up!"

    nrt "Maybe once upon a time you could’ve offered enough for Lillian to at least catch her gaze on you for a moment or two before deciding better of it. Now you’re not even worth that."

    show l_sa_sp with dissolve
    lil "Nat? Is everything alright?"
    hide l_sa_sp
    show l_sa 

    nth su_bl "(Ah shit, that was out loud wasn’t it.)"

    nat su_bl_sp "Oh, h-hey Lillian."

    nat ne_sp "I’m OK I was just…"

    nth ne_sd "(Think of something think of something think of something.)"

    nat sa_ec_sp "Having a bad dream."

    hide l_sa
    show l_n_sp 
    lil "Oh. I’m sorry, you sounded quite distressed."
    hide l_n_sp
    show l_sy

    nrt "More like you’re so desperate for her attention that you started crying like a cat pretending she hasn’t been fed."

    nat ap_sp "Sorry, I didn’t mean to bother you."

    hide l_sy
    show l_sa_sp 
    lil "Are you feeling any better?"
    hide l_sa_sp
    show l_sy 

    nrt "Lillian moves in closer, standing by your bed. Her bed. The bed that you are currently in which belongs to her. She’s gazing down at you with that same gentle concern you’ve become depressingly used to."

    nat ne_sp "I guess physically, a little?"

    nat ne_sp "My head’s not spinning as much and I can actually feel my legs, mostly."

    nat dj_sm_sp "Emotionally, though?"

    nrt "You let out a bitter laugh that Lillian doesn’t share."

    nat ap_sp "Sorry, that was shitty of me."

    nat sa_sp "You’ve already been doing so much for me, and here I am fishing for sympathy."

    hide l_sy
    show l_n_sp 
    lil "Nonsense. I asked how you were doing, and you answered the question honestly."

    hide l_n_sp
    show l_sa_sp
    lil "Would you… like to talk about it?"
    hide l_sa_sp
    show l_sy

    nth ag_sd "(No.)"

    nth ne_sd_bl "(But also yes, more than anything.)"

    nth sa_ec "(I fucking hate being gay.)"

    nat sa_sp "I mean, I guess you already got the idea last night, from what you were saying."

    hide l_sy
    show l_n_sp
    lil "Roughly speaking, yes."

    lil "Your job sucked, your family are worse, and your life as a whole wasn’t exactly where you’d hoped it would be?"
    hide l_n_sp
    show l_sy 

    nat ne_sp "I’d probably put the job below my family, but yeah pretty much."

    hide l_sy
    show l_n_sp 
    lil "You know you’re allowed to want things to be better for yourself, right Natalie?"
    hide l_n_sp
    show l_sy

    nat su_sp "Huh?"

    hide l_sy
    show l_n_sp
    lil "Just because you were miserable yesterday, it doesn’t mean you deserved to feel that way. Or that you can’t wish to feel better today."

    hide l_n_sp
    show l_sa_sp
    lil "I’ve… noticed how reluctant you are to accept help from me."
    hide l_sa_sp
    show l_sa 

    nat sa_sp "Oh. Shit, sorry Lillian, I didn’t mean—"

    hide l_sa
    show l_n_s_sp
    lil "I’m not upset with you, Nat."

    hide l_n_s_sp
    show l_sy
    lil "Of course, I’d love it if you were able to happily accept my help without beating yourself up over it, but then you wouldn’t be in a position to need any help in the first place, would you?"
        
    nat su_sp "I... guess?"
    nat ne_s_sp "I really do appreciate everything you've been doing for me. Not just cause you're such an amazing cook."

    hide l_sy
    show l_h

    nrt "Lillian smiles beautifully, and you probably think you're sooo smooth right now, don't you?"

    hide l_h
    show l_h_sp 
    lil "Well then, just know that I'm always happy to help with whatever you need, and you're always welcome here, Natalie. Especially if you keep being such a sweetie."

    hide l_h_sp
    show l_h 

    nth sh_bl "(Oh god oh fuck if she's not careful I'm gonna get {i}seriously{/i} down bad.)"

    nrt "She sounds so genuine, so reassuring, that you almost forget for a moment just how absurd it is that she's offering this to {b}you{/b} of all people."

    nat ne_sd_bl_sp "Careful, I might get ideas."
    nat ne_sd_bl_sp "You're gonna get sick of me if I'm here every day."

    hide l_h
    show l_fl_sp
    lil "Well, we'll just have to find out then, won't we?"

    hide l_fl_sp
    show l_h_bl

    nrt "Lillian laughs at that, full of music and delight. You could lose yourself completely in that laugh. "
    nrt "Hell, you're already losing yourself in the fantasy of actually taking her up on her joke offer. Visiting every day, becoming part of the furniture, sharing meals cooked by a gorgeous woman who actually gives a shit you exist."

    nrt "No, by your {b}friend,{/b} you ridiculous horndog. Even if it's insane she considers herself that, the least you can do is treat her appropriately."

    nat ne_s_sp "Well, I guess if I'm gonna be around more often, can I just say this place is {i}amazing?{/i}"

    hide l_h_bl
    show l_su_sp
    lil "You think so?"

    hide l_su_sp
    show l_h_sp
    lil "Well, it's nice to have someone to share it with, then."

    hide l_h_sp
    show l_h

    nat h_sp "Beats my place anyway. If I was having you over I'd have to spend a month clearing it up and it {i}still{/i} wouldn't look anywhere near this good!"

    nrt "Girl {b}why{/b} are you saying this."

    hide l_h
    show l_n_s_sp
    lil "Well, you needn't worry about that."

    hide l_n_s_sp
    show l_n_s 

    nat ne_s_sp "So true. Hey, I know I've been in this room all day but I've spent most of that asleep and the bits I've been awake I've been—"

    nth shy_b "{cps=100}(Don't say looking at you don't say looking at you don't say looking at you.){/cps}"

    nat ne_sd_bl_sp "—A little woozy."

    nth ne_s_sd_bl "(Close enough.)"

    nat ne_s_sp "You mind if I have a look around?"

    hide l_n_s
    show l_h_sp
    lil "By all means!"

    hide l_h_sp
    show l_n_s

    nrt "You cast your gaze across the room, looking for a conversation starter. The taxidermy butterflies seem a pretty obvious place to start."

    nrt "The shockingly well-preserved butterflies dominate the decorations, interspersed with a smattering of pressed leaves, fragments of fossils, and globs of amber that, upon closer inspection, you can see ancient insects frozen inside."

    nat su_sp "Did you make all these yourself?"

    hide l_n_s
    show l_h_sp
    lil "Well, given that I'm not a forty million year old tree, not quite."

    hide l_h_sp
    show l_h

    nrt "She laughs gently, and you feel like the stupidest woman to ever live."

    hide l_h
    show l_n_s_sp
    lil "But I've been assembling this collection for years now. I started with the leaves, when I was still a child. All of my first efforts have wilted away by now, I didn't learn the proper techniques for preserving them for a good while..."

    hide l_n_s_sp
    show l_n_s 

    nrt "She trails off, wistfully reminiscing. You almost don't want to break the moment, preserved in amber like those unfortunate yet immortal insects on the wall. But your curiosity finally gets the better of you."

    nat ne_sp "And the butterflies?"

    hide l_n_s
    show l_n_s_sp
    lil "Oh yes, those I preserved and pinned myself. They're beautiful, aren't they?"

    nat ne_s_sp "Gorgeous, yeah..."

    lil "I've always loved butterflies, but they can't be kept as pets, sadly."

    nat su_sp "Really?"
    hide l_n_s_sp
    show l_sa_sp
    lil "Any enclosed space is too small for them. They will find the edges, and fly into them over and over, until their wings break from the exertion."

    nat sa_sp "Oh... That's a shame."

    hide l_sa_sp
    show l_n_s_sp 
    lil "Yes, but thankfully I've found that I love preserving them just as much. Perhaps even more."

    hide l_n_s_sp
    show l_n_s

    nat su_sp "How {i}do{/i} you preserve them?"

    hide l_n_s
    show l_n_s_sp
    lil "Well, typically you have to begin by rehydrating the specimen. Butterflies' wings and bodies become brittle after their deaths, especially given that freezing is the preferred method of humanely killing them."

    hide l_n_s_sp
    show l_n_s

    nrt "She says the {b}killing them{/b} part so matter of fact that it makes you feel like the weirdo for how quickly your brain latches onto it."
    nrt "Does she kill the butterflies herself? Raise them from caterpillars to grant a beautiful death? Or is she just talking about entomological best practices?"

    nrt "You don't know enough about butterflies to know if these would be the kinds that she would have just found dead in the wild, although you don't see any little pots with growing caterpillars lying around either. "
    nrt "You're not sure if that comforts you or not, or if it's even supposed to."
    hide l_n_s
    show l_n_s_sp
    lil "There are a few different methods for rehydrating."
    lil "The safest is to place them in a sealed box with damp paper towels, but injecting them with boiling water can make them easier to work with, if you have the skill to do so without causing any damage."

    lil "Once the specimen is rehydrated, you place an insect pin through the thorax and into the mounting board, then you use a combination of forceps and smaller pins to arrange the wings and legs into position."

    hide l_n_s_sp
    show l_h_sp
    lil "After that, it's simply a matter of letting them dry out again, carefully removing the pins, and sealing them in the display case."

    hide l_h_sp
    show l_n_s_sp
    lil "I also have to be quite careful with the temperature and humidity settings in the flat, to avoid damaging the specimens."

    hide l_n_s_sp
    show l_n_s

    nat ne_sd_sp "That's... a lot, wow."

    nrt "You'd initially wanted to ask more about the butterflies. What species, where they're from. "
    nrt "But you're worried that digging too deep there will lead to you getting answers you don't want to know about Lillian's willingness to freeze butterflies to death for decoration."

    nrt "Which is a weird thing to worry about. You're not a vegetarian, you just ate a bunch of meat from dead pigs earlier today without a second thought."

    nrt "People kill bugs all the time, hell, most actual vegetarians have to live with the fact farmers spray pesticides everywhere to stop bugs from eating all the veggies before people can."

    nrt "You wouldn't care if Lillian went fishing, baiting hooks with worms by the dozen. Why does it matter if she freezes some butterflies?"

    nrt "You can't think of a good answer to that question, so instead you cast your glance around for anything to change the conversation."
    hide l_n_s
    scene waterfall with fade

    nrt "A photo of yellow butterflies catches your eye, set against a gorgeous backdrop of a luscious green valley and torrents of cascading water."

    nat ne_s_sp "That photo's absolutely beautiful."

   

    lil "Why thank you, I took it myself!"
    lil "I was on a family holiday after my graduation, actually. "
    lil "My grandparents were extremely gracious to allow me to spend a few days of the trip heading out to Yunnan, I was almost worried I wouldn't get any good photos before I had to head back to Shanghai."

    scene bed_day with fade
    show l_h_sp
    lil "The scenery there is utterly breathtaking. Despite my best efforts, the pictures truly don't do it justice."

    hide l_h_sp
    show l_n_s

    nrt "Shit. Shit shit shit."

    nrt "You're hoping Lillian's too caught in her reminiscence over the photo to notice your breath quickening, the panic rising in your features."

    nrt "Of {i}course{/i} she took the pictures in fucking China. If you actually knew anything about China you probably would have known all about the famous butterfly valley of Yunnan."
    nrt "So the fact you {i}don't{/i} is just going to make it even more obvious you've never been, and the whole series of dominoes is gonna come tumbling right down."

    hide l_n_s
    show l_sa_sp
    lil "Natalie? Is everything alright?"

    hide l_sa_sp
    show l_sa

    nrt "{b}Shit{/b} she noticed."

    nrt "Think of something you idiot! Any second now she's going to say something that forces you to tell her the truth."

    nat ne_sd_sp "Um, sorry I didn't know about it. Never been."

    hide l_sa
    show l_n_sp
    lil "Hm? You have nothing to apologise for, I already assumed as much."

    hide l_n_sp
    show l_n

    nat ap_sp "I guess Yunnan's pretty out of the way, haha."

    hide l_n
    show l_su_sp
    lil "That's... not what I meant?"
    hide l_su_sp
    show l_n

    nrt "{b}SHIT!{/b}"
    nrt "You quickly try to scour your memory. Have you ever told her anything that would give away that you're adopted?"
    nrt "She's been speaking to you in English, but that's normal, right?"
    nrt "Her accent's British enough that she's almost certainly born and raised here, most second or third generationers stick to English with each other, Chinese with their parents, right?"

    nrt "You don't remember ever having any spicy food around her. You had the same drink as her last night. You never—"

    nth dj_sm "(Wait. {i}My fucking surname!{/i})"

    nrt "Oh. Yes."

    nrt "Natalie Jackson, you goddamn idiot."

    # Music cuts out

    nat ne_sd_sp "Yeah, um, you've probably figured it out but I've... never actually been to China."

    nat ap_sp "Guess you could say I'm not really in touch with that part of my family tree, haha."

    hide l_n
    show l_n_sp
    lil "Oh. Yes, I surmised as much."

    hide l_n_sp
    show l_n

    nat ap_sp "Honestly I dunno why I even tried to hide it, or ever thought I could."

    nat ne_sd_sp "But... yeah."

    nat ne_sp "I'm adopted."

    jump schoolback3